I agree with Stuart here.

Unfortunately, this change is doing way more than just fixing a bug. It's doing a major refactor of this logic and I'd personally like to avoid that.

Would it be possible to go closer to the previous version and fix the issue there with a smaller change?

One more thing that confuses me is that this change has a blueprint assigned and I believe that's misleading. Furthermore, the blueprint is not approved and that will block this fix. :/
